                     <title xml:lang="he">שטר</title>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Acquittance of debt by Jacob ben Moses and Margaret (named in the Latin charter on the other side) to Peter of Edgefield (a parish in Norfolk). </p>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Latin charter is a chirograph bond by Peter de Eclisfeld to Margaret, daugther of Jurnet [of Norwich], to pay 5 silver marks on the second Midsummer day after the death of Gerard, Prior of Norwich [ob. 1201]. (See description in Anglo-Jewish Historical Exhibition Royal Albert Hall. 1887. Catalogue, p. 184.)</p>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
						
                  
                  
                  
